ntsync 1011: NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_TRY_RECV2 — non-blocking RECV2

Add a non-blocking variant of CHANNEL_RECV2 that returns -EAGAIN
immediately when the channel's pending queue is empty rather than
blocking in wait_event_interruptible_exclusive.

Motivation: gamma channel dispatcher burst-drain optimization.
Today the dispatcher loop is

  AGG_WAIT -> CHANNEL_RECV2 -> dispatch -> CHANNEL_REPLY -> back to AGG_WAIT

3 ioctls per dispatched entry.  Under burst (paint storm, library
scan, plugin instantiation) the second AGG_WAIT returns immediately
because channel.depth > 0, but it is still a syscall.  With
TRY_RECV2 the dispatcher can drain the pending queue in a tight
loop, returning to AGG_WAIT only when the queue is actually empty:

  AGG_WAIT -> loop { TRY_RECV2; if EAGAIN break; dispatch; REPLY } -> back to AGG_WAIT

For N entries in a burst, syscall count drops from 3N to 1 + 2N —
saves one AGG_WAIT per entry past the first.

Implementation: refactor ntsync_channel_recv2 to take a `bool nonblock`
parameter.  When true and pending is empty, kfree(new_ep) and return
-EAGAIN before entering wait_event_interruptible_exclusive.  Add
NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_TRY_RECV2 (_IOWR('N', 0x98, ...)) that dispatches
through the inner function with nonblock=true; existing
NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_RECV2 dispatches with nonblock=false (unchanged
semantics).

ABI: purely additive.  Same args struct as RECV2 (no UAPI breakage).
Pre-1011 kernels return -ENOTTY for the new ioctl; userspace falls
back to the existing blocking path.

PREEMPT_RT discipline: no new locks, no new allocations on the
non-block fast path beyond the same kzalloc(new_ep) RECV2 already
does (kfree'd before -EAGAIN return).  obj_lock window is unchanged
(non-block branch exits before re-acquiring after the empty check).
Same wait_wq, same exclusive-wait semantics for the blocking path.

NT semantics: TRY_RECV2 is purely a kernel-level optimization — the
RECV2-on-fire NT-correct semantics (mutex acquire, auto-event reset,
etc.) don't apply because channels are notify-only objects already.

---
---
--- a/include/uapi/linux/ntsync.h
+++ b/include/uapi/linux/ntsync.h
@@ -157,6 +157,29 @@
 #define NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_RECV2	_IOWR('N', 0x96, struct ntsync_channel_recv2_args)
 
 /*
+ * NSPA 1011: NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_TRY_RECV2.
+ *
+ * Identical to NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_RECV2 (same args struct, same OUT
+ * fields) but returns -EAGAIN immediately when the channel's pending
+ * queue is empty — never blocks the caller in
+ * wait_event_interruptible_exclusive.
+ *
+ * Use case: gamma channel dispatcher draining multiple entries per
+ * AGGREGATE_WAIT cycle.  Under burst load (paint storm, library scan,
+ * plugin instantiation) the dispatcher would otherwise pay one full
+ * AGG_WAIT round-trip per entry; with TRY_RECV2 it can drain the
+ * pending queue in a tight loop, returning to AGG_WAIT only when
+ * empty.  Reduces per-entry syscall count from 3 (AGG_WAIT + RECV2 +
+ * REPLY) to 2 (TRY_RECV2 + REPLY) on every entry past the first in
+ * a burst.
+ *
+ * Purely additive: existing NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_RECV2 path is
+ * unchanged.  Pre-1011 kernels return -ENOTTY → userspace falls back
+ * to the blocking RECV2 path.
+ */
+#define NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_TRY_RECV2	_IOWR('N', 0x98, struct ntsync_channel_recv2_args)
+
+/*
  * NSPA: Heterogeneous aggregate wait — patch 1010.
  *
  * Wait atomically on N ntsync objects + M file descriptors + optional
--- a/drivers/misc/ntsync.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/ntsync.c
@@ -1770,7 +1770,7 @@
  * to keep the diff small and the read order obvious; the extra field copy
  * is the only behavioural difference.
  */
-static int ntsync_channel_recv2(struct ntsync_obj *ch, void __user *argp)
+static int ntsync_channel_recv2(struct ntsync_obj *ch, void __user *argp, bool nonblock)
 {
 	struct ntsync_channel_recv2_args args;
 	struct ntsync_channel_entry *e = NULL;
@@ -1789,6 +1789,16 @@
 	obj_lock(ch);
 	while (RB_EMPTY_ROOT(&ch->u.channel.pending)) {
 		obj_unlock(ch);
+		/* NSPA 1011: TRY_RECV2 (nonblock=true) returns -EAGAIN
+		 * immediately when pending is empty rather than blocking
+		 * the dispatcher in wait_event_interruptible_exclusive.
+		 * Used for the burst-drain optimization — caller can
+		 * tight-loop TRY_RECV2 until -EAGAIN, then go back to
+		 * AGGREGATE_WAIT for the next channel-fired event. */
+		if (nonblock) {
+			kfree(new_ep);
+			return -EAGAIN;
+		}
 		/* See exclusive-wait commentary in ntsync_channel_recv. */
 		ret = wait_event_interruptible_exclusive(ch->u.channel.recv_wq,
 			!RB_EMPTY_ROOT(&ch->u.channel.pending));
@@ -2059,7 +2069,9 @@
 	case NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_DEREGISTER_THREAD:
 		return ntsync_channel_deregister_thread(obj, argp);
 	case NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_RECV2:
-		return ntsync_channel_recv2(obj, argp);
+		return ntsync_channel_recv2(obj, argp, false);
+	case NTSYNC_IOC_CHANNEL_TRY_RECV2:
+		return ntsync_channel_recv2(obj, argp, true);
 	default:
 		return -ENOIOCTLCMD;
 	}
